// GNU-ton boss arena ‚ÄĒ tall underground chamber for the giant wildebeest fight.
//
// Rev: bumped to 1792√ó1280 (was 1536√ó896) so the player drops in from a
// ledge near the top and sees the whole GNU-ton silhouette before
// descending into striking range. The body sprite is z-layered behind
// platforms (see `presentation::rendering::actors::GnuTonBodyLayer`)
// so the player can read jump targets through the giant.
//
// Encounter flow:
//   1. Player enters from `hall_of_bosses` via the top-left LoadingZone.
//   2. Lands on the entry ledge, walks right onto a BreakablePlatform.
//   3. The platform breaks under their weight, forcing a descent into
//      the fight (they fall through a column of perches that catches
//      them safely before the floor).
//   4. Boss fight at floor level. GNU-ton's head is always damageable
//      but high up at rest ‚ÄĒ climb the perches to reach it, or wait for
//      the head-descent windows that bring it to player level.
//   5. After defeat, the player climbs back up the ladder column near
//      the spawn (the ladder is painted Climbable in IntGrid).
//
// Layout (1792 wide x 1280 tall):
//
//   +------------------------------------------------------------+ y=0
//   |‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí ceiling ‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí|
//   | [door]   [ledge‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ][BreakablePad]                          | ‚Üź top entry
//   |  ‚Ėďladder‚Ėď                                                  |
//   |  ‚Ėďladder‚Ėď               ‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎtop perch‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎ                  |
//   |  ‚Ėďladder‚Ėď                                                  |
//   |  ‚Ėďladder‚Ėď        ‚ĒĆ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ[BossSpawn]‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚Ēź                   | ‚Üź GNU-ton centered
//   |  ‚Ėďladder‚Ėď        ‚Ēā   (220√ó220 box)     ‚Ēā                   |
//   |  ‚Ėďladder‚Ėď        ‚ĒĒ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚Ēė                   |
//   |  ‚Ėďladder‚Ėď   ‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎperch left       perch right‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎ               |
//   |  ‚Ėďladder‚Ėď                                                  |
//   |  ‚Ėďladder‚Ėď       ‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎperch mid-left   perch mid-right‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎ       |
//   |  ‚Ėďladder‚Ėď                                                  |
//   |  ‚Ėďladder‚Ėď                                                  |
//   |  ‚Ėďfloor ‚Ėď‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎperch left low    perch right low‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎ             |
//   |‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí floor ‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí‚Ėí| y=1248
//   +------------------------------------------------------------+
//
// Ladder gating: the Climbable IntGrid below is painted unconditionally
// at world-load time, but the sandbox-side `gate_gnu_ton_arena_ladder`
// system (boss_encounter/gnu_ton.rs) removes the Ladder regions from
// `world.climbable_regions` on entry and re-adds them the frame the
// gnu_ton boss is defeated. So the cells exist in LDtk but only count
// at runtime once the player has earned the retreat.

